{
  "stem": "3874.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The good thing I did, is I surreptitiously went through my parents' picture album and took out photos of different people who were dear to me-- my grandparents, my parents, and my aunts and uncles.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It is the only thing that I really have left of my parents.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Most of the other children who came to France didn't do that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And most of them don't have any kind of records or any kind of pictures.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But I carried those pictures with me throughout my-- until I came to the United States.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And of course, I have them today.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The other thing which I did, that I remember very well, are writing a sort of a farewell letter, and leaving it in my-- in my room.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I specifically remember things like, where I said, today I'm 10 years old, and I must leave my parents' house.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I found out later on that when my mother had read the letter, she actually--she absolutely came apart.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I mean, she really, it really affected her.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "To this day, it may have been a childish thing to do, but I recognized even at that time that we have to get out, that, otherwise, some bad things are going to happen.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I wrote the letter saying, at this young age, I had to leave my parents' house.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And it's-- that letter-- even though I don't have a copy of the letter, obviously, but the thought has just followed me around, especially after I found out the reaction of my mother.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, March 14, 1939.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was in the transport-- I was put on the transport in the train in Vienna.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My parents and my brother came with me to train.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Of course, I, you know, we all stuck our heads out of the window.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
